What's stopping police from closing over one thousand 500 drug houses in the Western Cape? By mid- 2021 authorities confirmed that over half of these drugs dens were in the Cape Metro. Now, the province's Police Ombudsman is investigating why the SAPS can’t seem to shut them down. eNCA's Monique Mortlock has more details on this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Western Cape Police Ombudsman has launched an investigation into allegations of police inefficiencies in combating the drug trade and closing drug dens. By mid-2021 authorities confirmed that over half of these drugs dens were in the Cape Metro. The province's Police Ombudsman is investigating why the SAPS can’t seem to shut them down. READ: Drug dealer arrested in Cape Town Community leaders in drug hotspots believe the investigation could uncover corrupt cops. The Western Cape SAPS says it will cooperate with the probe by the Ombudsman. It says the drug scourge requires an all-around approach from all government entities.